here we have to return square of all element in the array in sorted order . but it have negative element as well . 

here brute force o(nlogn) is not accepted we have to make it o(n) without sorting the array ... that's the twist.
  simple approach but not accepted ... array elements are already sorted ... so if there is negative element its square will be postivie so after squaring all the element do sort them .


step 1 : square all element ans[i] = a[i]*a[i] : o(n)
  step 2 : sort them : o(nlogn)
vector<int> sq_ar(vector<int>& a){
    int n = a.size();
    vector<int> ans(n);
    for(int i = 0 ; i<n ; i++){
        ans[i] = a[i]*a[i];
    }
    sort(ans.begin(), ans.end());
    return ans ;
}
